<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-700-696  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 700 696  OV: 07 700 514.andM; </DOCID><JOURNAL>MacUser  Nov 1989 v5 n11 p124(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>RecordHolderPlus. (Software Review) (1 of 7 data-base managementsystems evaluations in 'In single file') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Landis, Ken.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Software Discoveries Inc's $99.95 RecordHolderPlus offers modestfunctionality at a very low price, performing slightly better thanits competitors in some categories and slightly worse in others.andO;Its strongest features are its editing capabilities, which includerange checks, alphanumeric field checks, uppercase conversions,preset punctuation patterns, and pop-up field lists.andP;  Theprogram's WYSIWYG report writer is simple but effective, and itsTable of Contents window provides a convenient visual directory offiles.andP;  Logical-searching abilities, line and box drawing forreports, multiple data formats, and good computed-fieldscapabilities enhance RecordHolderPlus' power, but macros andmultiple-file searching are significant omissions.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software Discoveries Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)RecordHolderPlus (Data base management system).andO;Topic:     Data base management systemsEvaluationData Management.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Sometimes a flat-file manager just won't do the job, and you have to tradeits ease of use for the dynamic connections of a relational database.andP;  Arelational system offers more-efficient data storage.andP;  Information such asname, address, and phone number is stored in one file for access by all thefiles that need that information.andP;  Using that file may be as easy as enteringa customer number into an invoice, which feeds the person's data into theinvoice, thereby saving space and avoiding duplicate data.andM;Another advantage of a relational database is the provision of a programminglanguage.andP;  Relational databases don't have to haveandM;programming or procedural languages, but the most-powerful ones, such as 4thDimension and Omnis 5, do.andP;  Languages let programmers automate functions,customize the interface, and give users a product that is more sharplydefined to meet their particular needs.andM;High-end relational databases add another feature that is critical in acorporate setting and that most flat-file databases (other than FileMaker II)don't have: truefile- and record-locking capability.andP;  This feature makes thedatabase truly multiuser and ensures that only one copy of the database ismaintained.andO;</TEXT></DOC>